PREHEAT oven to 350 degrees F. Grease a 9-inch pie plate. PRESS 3/4-package cookie dough onto bottom and sides of prepared pie plate. BAKE for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown; flatten down with back of spoon to form pie shell. Cool completely on wire rack. SPREAD 1/4 cup peanut butter over crust. Mix ice cream, remaining peanut butter and 1/4 cup peanuts in a medium bowl. Spoon into cookie crust; spread evenly. Drizzle with Nesquik(tm) and additional peanuts. Freeze for at least 2 hours or overnight. BAKE remaining cookie dough according to package directions. Cool completely on wire rack; crumble cookies. THAW pie for 5 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle cookie crumbs over pie; cut into wedges.